org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.allocations

Interface Allocate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AllocateImpl

    public interface Allocate
extends DirectedRelationshipPropertyPath
    A representation of the model object 'Allocate'. Allocate is a dependency based on UML::abstraction. It is a mechanism for associating elements of different types, or in different hierarchies, at an abstract level. Allocate is used for assessing user model consistency and directing future design activity. It is expected that an «allocate» relationship between model elements is a precursor to a more concrete relationship between the elements, their properties, operations, attributes, or sub-classes.

    The following features are supported:

    • Base Abstraction
    See Also:
